Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(halved, peeled and chopped into small pieces).

Halve the @bell pepper{2%units}(halved, cored and chopped into 1cm chunks) and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 1cm chunks.

Chop the @sweet potato{1%unit}(chopped into 1cm chunks) and @carrot{1%unit}(chopped into 1cm chunks) into 1cm chunks.

Place a #pot{} over high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once the oil is hot, fry the @Irish bacon lardons{100%g} until golden, ~{3-5%minutes}, stirring regularly.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook lardons thoroughly.

Remove the lardons from the pot.

Drizzle with @maple syrup{15%g} and toss to coat.

Return the pot to medium-high heat with a knob of @butter{to taste}.

When melted, add the onion, pepper, garlic and @paprika{2%sachets} to the pot and fry until softened stirring occasionally, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add the sweet potato, carrot, @chicken stock{1%sachet}, @Hello Muscat{1%sachet}, @salt{1/2%tsp} (per 2P) and @water{500%ml} (per 2P).

Bring to a boil then cover and lower heat to medium.

Cover and simmer until sweet potato and carrot are fork tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Once the soup is cooked, add half the @creme fraiche{65%g} and blend until smooth and creamy.

Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if you feel the soup is too thick.

Just before serving, pop the @baguette{2%units} into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Divide the soup between #bowls{}.

Add the remaining creme fraiche on top.

For a spooky presentation, drizzle the creme fraiche in concentric circles on the soup. Drag a sorcerer's wand (or #toothpick{}) from the centre to the ends, to create a spider's web.

Top with glazed bacon lardons on the outer side of the spider web.

Serve with the warm baguette on the side for dipping.